The article discusses the Immigration Accountability Executive Action taken by President Obama. The executive actions aim to secure the border, hold undocumented immigrants accountable, and ensure fairness in the immigration system. The actions include cracking down on illegal immigration at the border, prioritizing the deportation of felons, requiring undocumented immigrants to pass background checks and pay taxes, and streamlining legal immigration. The article also highlights the efforts made by the Obama administration to secure the border and reduce illegal border crossings. The actions taken by the President are within his legal authority, but Congress is needed to pass a comprehensive bill to fully address the issue. The article concludes by mentioning various measures to strengthen border security, crack down on companies hiring undocumented workers, create a path to citizenship for eligible immigrants, boost the economy, and simplify the legal immigration process.